The paper is primarily focused on the design and optimization of column stores, which are a type of database management system (DBMS). Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with data structures and compression schemes, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of circuits and operators in the model suggests a connection to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and the focus on optimization and parallelization suggests a connection to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
